1. Using the echo command print in console "Hello World". Here is some info about echo command [https://discuss.codecademy.com/t/what-are-practical-uses-of-the-echo-command/394788]

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % echo Hello World!
Hello World!


2. Create a new directory called new_dir.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % mkdir new_dir
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % ls
exercices	lorem		new_dir		readme.md
inputs		lorem-copy	outputs

3.Delete/Remove the directory new_dir.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % rm -r new_dir
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % ls
exercices	lorem		outputs
inputs		lorem-copy	readme.md

4. Copy the file sed.txt from the lorem folder and paste it to the folder lorem-copy folder.

/Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % ls
at.txt		lorem-copy	lorem.txt
at.txte		lorem-copy1	sed.txt
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cp -R /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem/sed.txt /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem-copy
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % pwd
/Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cd ..
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % cd lorem-copy
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem-copy % ls
dummy_file.txt	sed.txt
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem-copy % 

5. Copy the other two files from the lorem folder to lorem-copy folder in just one line using semicolon ;.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % pwd
/Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cp -R /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem/at.txt /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem-copy
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cp -R /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem/lorem.txt /Users/jxhn/lab-bash/lorem-copy

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cd ..
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % cd lorem-copy
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem-copy % ls
at.txt		dummy_file.txt	lorem.txt	sed.txt

