15. List all files with the extension .txt in lorem folder.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % find . -type f -name "*.txt"
./at.txt
./lorem.txt
./sed.txt
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % 

16. Count the rows in sed.txt file from lorem folder. Look concatenate cat and wc with the pipe |.

/Users/jxhn/Desktop/IRONHACK/lab-bash/lorem
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % cat /Users/jxhn/Desktop/IRONHACK/lab-bash/lorem/sed.txt | wc -l
       9
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lorem % 

17. Count the files which start with lorem in all directories.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % ls -dq *lorem* | wc -l
       2
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP lab-bash % 

Bonus: 
20: Store your name in a variable with read command.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % read
Jahn Nazari
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % echo $REPLY
Jahn Nazari
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % 

21. 

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % read
Jahn Nazari
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % echo $REPLY
Jahn Nazari
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % 

22. Create a new directory named with variable name.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % mkdir $REPLY
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % ls
Jahn Nazari
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % 

23. Remove that directory.

(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % rm -rf $REPLY
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % ls
(base) jxhn@Jahns-MBP outputs % 
